ARTICLE IX ADDENDUM — MEDINA MEMORY SDK

  A9.1  CONFIDENTIALITY DESIGNATION

        This package is classified at the HIGHEST CONFIDENTIALITY level
        within the MEDINA intelligence architecture. It contains the
        core memory temple, lineage tracking, memory ring, and phi-
        traced persistence systems that form the foundational memory
        substrate of the entire sovereign intelligence.

  A9.2  AUTHORIZED USE — INTERNAL ONLY

        (a) This package is authorized exclusively for internal use
            by Alfredo "Freddy" Medina Hernandez and persons or
            entities holding a valid MEDINA Enterprise License
            Agreement (MELA) signed by the Author.

        (b) No evaluation, trial, or preview access is permitted
            without a fully executed MELA.

        (c) Internal use means: deployment within the Author's own
            infrastructure, or within an enterprise licensee's
            infrastructure solely for the licensee's own internal
            business operations.

  A9.3  ENTERPRISE LICENSE TERMS

        (a) Enterprise licenses are available solely at the Author's
            discretion and only after execution of a MELA.

        (b) Each MELA shall specify: deployment scope, permitted
            instance count, data residency requirements, audit
            rights, and annual license fee.

        (c) No enterprise licensee may sublicense, redistribute, or
            expose this package or its APIs to third parties.

  A9.4  ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS (IN ADDITION TO ARTICLE III)

        (a) No portion of this package's memory architecture, ring
            system, lineage algorithms, or phi-traced persistence
            methods may be studied, documented, or described to any
            third party for any purpose.

        (b) No integration with external memory systems, databases,
            or caching layers is permitted without written approval.

        (c) No benchmarking, performance testing, or comparative
            analysis results may be published or shared.

  A9.5  TRADE SECRET DESIGNATION

        All algorithms, data structures, and architectural patterns
        in this package constitute trade secrets of the highest order
        under DTSA and TUTSA. Misappropriation will be prosecuted to
        the maximum extent permitted by law, including criminal
        referral under 18 U.S.C. § 1832.

